## Phase 0 — Instrument calibration model

### ✅ Done

- [x] `WelfordAccumulator` — online mean + variance, numerically stable
- [x] `LinearRegressionAccumulator` — online per-pixel linear regression
      using Welford-centred bivariate formulation (eliminates catastrophic
      cancellation in slope and residual SS)
- [x] `InstrumentModel` dataclass with fields for all calibration outputs
- [x] `fit_bias` — Welford streaming fit, produces `bias_mean`, `read_noise`
- [x] `fit_dark` — streaming linear regression, produces `dark_rate`,
      `hot_pixel_mask` via MAD-based threshold
- [x] `fit_flat` — Welford streaming fit with per-channel Bayer normalisation
      for OSC cameras; produces `flat_gain`, `flat_uncertainty`
- [x] `fit_dark_flat` — Welford mean of residuals, produces `amp_glow_profile`
- [x] `fit_all` — top-level entry point, discovers frames by subfolder name
      or FITS `IMAGETYP` header keyword
- [x] `calibrate_frame` — applies bias/dark/flat corrections to a raw frame
- [x] `validate` — sanity checks with logged warnings
- [x] `is_compatible` — checks shape, gain, temperature before cross-session reuse
- [x] HDF5 serialization — `save` / `load` round-trip
- [x] Auto chunk sizing from available RAM via `psutil`
- [x] OSC Bayer pattern detection from FITS header (`BAYERPAT`, `COLORTYP`)
- [x] Scope geometry fields as placeholders:
      `aperture_mm`, `focal_length_mm`, `central_obstruction`, `pixel_size_um`
- [x] PSF placeholder fields:
      `psf_diffraction` (None), `psf_optics` (None), `position_angle_deg` (None)

