## Phase 0b — Bayesian prior hierarchy for calibration (`bayes_calibration.py`)

### ✅ Done

- [x] `SensorPriors` dataclass — published sensor spec defaults with factory
      `for_asi533_gain100()` (read noise 6 ADU, dark 0.002 ADU/s at -10°C)
- [x] `BiasPriorAccumulator` — Gaussian-Gaussian conjugate in information
      (precision) form; streaming update per frame; prior_mean + prior_variance
- [x] `ReadNoisePriorAccumulator` — InverseGamma conjugate; accumulates
      α += 0.5 and β += 0.5·(x-μ)² per frame; Choi-Wette initialised
- [x] `DarkRatePriorAccumulator` — Gamma-Poisson conjugate; accumulates
      α += x_counts and β += exposure_s per frame; prior initialised from
      sensor spec rate and concentration
- [x] `FlatGainPriorAccumulator` — Gaussian conjugate in precision form;
      accounts for Poisson shot noise + read noise in likelihood variance;
      prior mean ALWAYS reset to 1.0 on new session (gain mean is not reusable),
      prior variance (pixel-to-pixel gain structure) carries over
- [x] `dark_rate_temperature_correction()` — Arrhenius scaling for silicon;
      E_g = 1.12 eV; round-trip A→B→A = identity to 1e-6 relative
- [x] `DarkRatePriorAccumulator.temperature_correct()` — scales α in-place
      (β stays in seconds); updates ref_temp_c
- [x] `BayesCalibrationState` — container for all four accumulators with
      point-estimate properties (bias_mean, read_noise, dark_rate, flat_gain)
- [x] `BayesCalibrationState.from_priors()` — construct all four accumulators
      from SensorPriors; logs prior parameters
- [x] HDF5 serialization under `/bayes/` group — appends to same file as
      InstrumentModel; stores full posterior params (α,β or μ,τ²), not
      just point estimates; lossless cross-session accumulation
- [x] `BayesCalibrationState.load(new_session=True, new_temp_c=...)` —
      resets frame counts, resets flat gain mean, temperature-corrects dark prior
- [x] `BayesCalibrationState.load(new_session=False)` — resume interrupted
      session: all counts and posteriors preserved unchanged
- [x] `BayesCalibrationState.summary()` — prints posterior median + n for all
      four parameters

### 🔲 Planned

- [ ] `fit_all(folder, prior=BayesCalibrationState)` integration — wire
      BayesCalibrationState into InstrumentModel.fit_all() as optional prior
- [ ] Temporal decay for hot pixel priors across sessions:
      α_prior_new = 1 + ρ·(α_post_old - 1); integrate with DarkMixtureModel

