## Phase 0c — Hot / cold pixel mixture model (`dark_mixture.py`)

### ✅ Done

- [x] `fit_dark_mixture()` — EM algorithm for 3-component Gamma mixture on
      dark_rate[H,W]; Choi-Wette + Newton-Raphson shape MLE per M-step;
      log-sum-exp stabilised E-step; component ordering enforced (hot > normal > cold)
- [x] `_gamma_shape_mle()` — Choi-Wette (1994) closed-form initial estimate
      followed by Newton-Raphson refinement using analytic trigamma
- [x] `_trigamma()` — recurrence + asymptotic expansion; accurate and fast
- [x] Initialisation from sensor mean rate: normal centred on spec,
      hot=10×, cold=0.1×; normal given higher initial concentration (α=5)
- [x] Convergence: relative ΔLL < tol; converges in 3–8 iterations in practice
- [x] `DarkMixtureModel` dataclass — pi[3], alpha[3], beta[3],
      class_probs[H,W,3], labels[H,W], log_likelihood_curve, normal_threshold
- [x] `pixel_weight_map()` — returns p_normal[H,W] as continuous reliability
      weight for the MAP stacker; no hard threshold
- [x] `calibrate_frame()` — returns both:
      (1) interpolated frame: hot/cold pixels replaced by neighbour-weighted
          average (neighbours weighted by their own p_normal);
      (2) weight_map: p_normal per pixel for MAP stacker
- [x] HDF5 serialization under `/dark_mixture/` group
- [x] Recovery of 336/338 true hot pixels (99.4%) on 256×256 synthetic data
      with π_hot=0.005
- [x] Edge case: all-normal dark map → π_normal > 0.95, n_hot=n_cold=0

