## Phase 1 — Instrument PSF characterisation (`optics.py`)

### ✅ Done

- [x] Placeholder fields for all PSF components in `InstrumentModel`
- [x] Three-component PSF decomposition design:
      `H_total = H_diff * H_optics * H_seeing`
- [x] `ScopeGeometry` dataclass — aperture, focal length, pixel size,
      central obstruction, effective wavelength; computes plate scale
      and Airy radius as properties
- [x] `compute_airy_psf()` — exact scalar diffraction formula via Bessel J₁;
      handles unobstructed and annular (obstructed) apertures; normalised to
      sum = 1.0; accepts plate scale override from WCS measurement
- [x] `compute_broadband_psf()` — integrates Airy over a wavelength grid
      weighted by QE × filter transmission curve
- [x] `get_instrument_psf()` — returns H_diff alone when psf_optics=None,
      H_diff * H_optics (FFT convolution) when optical aberration PSF available
- [x] `WCSGeometry` dataclass — position angle, plate scale, flip state,
      field centre RA/Dec, full WCS object
- [x] `extract_wcs_geometry()` — parses CD matrix (preferred), falls back to
      CDELT/CROTA2 and astropy pixel_scale_matrix; correct PA formula
      `atan2(CD1_2, CD2_2)`; supports all standard plate-solve header formats
- [x] `FrameShift` dataclass — sub-pixel dx/dy in pixels and arcsec,
      rotation angle, scale ratio between frames
- [x] `compute_frame_shift()` — derives sub-pixel shift + rotation + scale
      ratio between two WCS solutions using three test points; CRPIX-based
      shift model (correct); verified against known offsets to < 0.05 px
- [x] `ASTAPSolver` — subprocess wrapper for ASTAP plate solver with RA/Dec
      hint extraction from FITS header (handles HMS strings, degrees, hours);
      `solve()` invokes ASTAP and reads back updated header; `solve_from_header()`
      extracts WCS from already-solved frames without re-running ASTAP
- [x] PA convention documented and tested: 0° = North up, 90° = East up,
      verified at 0°/45°/90°/180°/270° against synthetic CD matrix headers

### 🔲 Provision only — not implementing soon

- [ ] `psf_optics[grid_y, grid_x, K, K]` — spatially varying optical
      aberration PSF estimated from artificial star or lucky imaging data
- [ ] 3×3 or 5×5 spatial grid of PSF estimates across sensor
- [ ] Bicubic interpolation of PSF grid between grid points
- [ ] Isolation of H_optics by deconvolving H_diff from best-seeing empirical PSFs

