## Phase 2 — Frame characterisation (`FrameCharacterizer`)

### 🔲 Planned

- [ ] `FrameCharacterizer` class — processes one light frame at a time
- [ ] ASTAP plate solve per frame → WCS solution
- [ ] Sub-pixel shift $W_i$ from WCS difference to reference frame
      (more accurate than mount encoder dither commands)
- [ ] Transparency $t_i$ from median stellar flux relative to reference frame
- [ ] Per-frame PSF fitting:
      - Extract 10–20 isolated unsaturated star stamps
      - Align stamps to sub-pixel centroid
      - Stack stamps → empirical $H_{\text{total},i}$
      - Fit Moffat profile: $H_\text{total}(r) = (\beta-1)/(\pi\alpha^2)(1 + r^2/\alpha^2)^{-\beta}$
      - Divide out instrument PSF → $H_{\text{seeing},i}$
      - Record FWHM$_i$ and $\beta_i$ as quality metrics
- [ ] Sky background estimation — 2D polynomial fit to source-masked pixels
- [ ] Per-frame quality score: FWHM, transparency, estimated SNR
- [ ] Output sufficient statistics for stacker accumulation:
      `shift`, `transparency`, `psf_kernel`, `sky_background` per frame

