## Phase 4 — Joint MAP optimisation (stacker core)

### 🔲 Planned

- [ ] PyTorch MAP optimiser on HR grid (2× super-resolution)
- [ ] Forward model: $t_i \cdot \text{FFT-conv}(H_i, W_i[\lambda])$ per frame
- [ ] Poisson negative log-likelihood loss
- [ ] Total Variation spatial prior with tunable weight $\alpha$
- [ ] Gamma-Poisson KL prior term with tunable weight $\beta$
- [ ] Adam optimiser, 100–300 iterations, ~5–15s on GPU for 9M pixels
- [ ] Non-negativity constraint: `lambda_.data.clamp_(min=0)` after each step
- [ ] Convergence monitoring — loss curve, FWHM of residuals
- [ ] Output: HR stacked image + per-pixel uncertainty map
- [ ] Batch processing: accumulate sufficient statistics frame-by-frame,
      never hold all frames in GPU memory simultaneously

### 🔲 Sub-pixel shift operators

- [ ] Bilinear interpolation shift operator $W_i$ in Fourier domain
      (phase shift theorem: shift by $(dx, dy)$ = multiply by
      $e^{-2\pi i (f_x dx + f_y dy)}$)
- [ ] OSC Bayer sub-pixel offsets — built-in diversity within each frame
      from R/G/B channel positions (no dithering required for some SR)
- [ ] Dither-based SR: use WCS-derived $W_i$ between frames

